Peel, halve and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces. Peel and grate the @ginger{1}(peeled and grated). Peel the @sweet potato{1}(peeled and chopped into 2cm chunks), then chop into 2cm chunks.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat. Add the onion. Cook until soft, ~{4-5%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Add the ginger, @Sri Lankan style curry powder{1} and @tomato puree{30}. Stir together and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Pour in the @water{300}, @coconut milk{200} and @vegetable stock paste{10}. Stir to combine.

Add the sweet potato and @red split lentils{100} to your pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Bring to a simmer, cover with a #lid{} and cook, stirring frequently, until the lentils and sweet potato are soft, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> TIP: If the dal is looking a little dry, just add a splash of water.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Zest and halve the @lime{1/2}. Pop the lime zest into a #bowl{} with the @dukkah mix{1} and coriander. Add the @olive oil{1}(for the salsa), a squeeze of lime juice and a pinch of salt and pepper. Mix together and leave to the side.

Meanwhile, heat a large #frying pan{} on high heat (don't add any oil). When the pan is hot, dry-fry your @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4} for ~{30%seconds} on each side. You want your tortillas to char slightly, so keep an eye on them. Transfer each tortilla to a #plate{}, making a chapati pile (spread each one with a little @?butter{}, if you have any). Keep them warm by covering the plate with #foil{}.

Once the dal is cooked, stir in the @king prawns{150} and simmer until cooked, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw seafood. The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Stir through the @baby spinach{100}, a handful at a time, until it has wilted, ~{1-2%minutes}. Squeeze in a little lime juice. Taste and add more salt, pepper or lime juice if you feel it needs it. Serve in #bowls{} with the dukkah salsa on top and the chapatis on the side. Enjoy!

> Step 6 MOD: If you've opted to get prawns with your dal, once the dal is cooked, stir in the prawns and simmer until cooked, 3-4 mins. Add the spinach and continue with the recipe as instructed.